Here are three targeted improvements that will reduce Python‐level dispatch and threading overhead for small n (e.g. n=20), and eliminate per‐call branching in the optimizer.  Together these should improve the 1 / riesz_energy_n20_s1 metric:

1) Remove `parallel=True` and switch `prange`→`range` in the hot Numba kernels for s=1 (this avoids thread‐spawn overhead when n is small).

2) Fold the `if s==1.0` test out of each energy+gradient call and pick the correct function once before calling `minimize`.

